## ğŸ” Explanation
In this level, a **service is running locally** on the machine and is
listening on **port 30000**.

The service expects the **password of the current level** as input.
If the correct password is provided, the service responds with the
**password for the next level**.

This demonstrates how services can communicate over network ports,
even on the same machine.

